The paper deals with mining topics from text corpora, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The use of category names to guide the topic mining process is a novel approach that can be applied to various NLP tasks, such as classification and lexical entailment. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as text embedding and iterative learning, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
